727026f-b.title: Queens: Jamaica Avenue - 149th Street
727026f-b.text:
Jamaica Ave., north side, opposite 149th Street,showing in a
set of four views the Hoyt house of 1891. Mrs. V.w. Mills was the
owner in 1873, and Thomas Adikes subsequent to 1891. Views 3 and
4 are more extensive, showing in addition to the Hoyt house others
in this area, all of which were gone in October 1928.
October 1923.
View 2: April 1925.
Views 3 \& 4: September, 1924.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

727025f-a.text:
Jamaica Avenue, at 149th AAtreet, viewing southeastward
toward the intersection from 90th Road (foreground). The
''gg' is on Jamaica Avenue and the 2-story taxpayer fronts

725888f-a.text:
149th Street, east side, between Jamaica and Archer Aves.,
showing the Kissam farmhouse, which does not appear in the 1931
Queens Atlas of Jamaica. If standing it would occupy lot 98, in
block 104O.
